<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="504">
diagnosis A medium-sized reddish yellow to brown member of the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33744" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole flavens Roger" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole flavens Roger" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavens">flavens</taxonomicName>
group; both major and minor are immediately recognizable by the large, &quot;sharkfin&quot; shape of the humerus in dorsal-oblique view, meaning that the anterior margin is straight and the posterior margin convex in profile, tipped with an acute or right angle. Very similar to 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181839" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole angulifera Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole angulifera Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angulifera">angulifera</taxonomicName>
, and in varying degree also to 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33595" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole arhuaca Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole arhuaca Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arhuaca">arhuaca</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181854" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole caulicola Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole caulicola Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caulicola">caulicola</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33662" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole chalca Wheeler" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole chalca Wheeler" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalca">chalca</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181857" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole chalcoides Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole chalcoides Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalcoides">chalcoides</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181903" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole mincana Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole mincana Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mincana">mincana</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33982" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole sagana Wheeler" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole sagana Wheeler" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sagana">sagana</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181949" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole tambopatae Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole tambopatae Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tambopatae">tambopatae</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34062" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole tragica Wheeler" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole tragica Wheeler" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tragica">tragica</taxonomicName>
in overall appearance but distinctive in the humeral shape and other traits in body shape, sculpture, pilosity, and color.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="504">Measurements (mm) Lectotype major: HW 0.94, HL 0.94, SL 0.46, EL 0.10, PW 0.48. Paralectotype minor: HW 0.50, HL 0.54, SL 0.58, EL 0.08, PW 0.34.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="504">
color Lectotype major of 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181939" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole schmalzi Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole schmalzi Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schmalzi">schmalzi</taxonomicName>
: body and appendages light brown, waist and gaster dark brown (
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33961" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole rehi Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole rehi Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rehi">rehi</taxonomicName>
syntype major is yellowish brown; 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33960" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole rata Borgmeier" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole rata Borgmeier" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rata">rata</taxonomicName>
syntype major is light reddish yellow).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="504">
Paralectotype minors of 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181939" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole schmalzi Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole schmalzi Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schmalzi">schmalzi</taxonomicName>
: body light to medium brown, appendages light brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="504">
Syntype minors of synonymous 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33961" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole rehi Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole rehi Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rehi">rehi</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33960" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole rata Borgmeier" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole rata Borgmeier" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rata">rata</taxonomicName>
: light brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
